title: For Sale:  Early model Winchester M1 Garand
postcontent:
I had purchased this rifle through CMP and have never shot it myself.  In my opinion, a rifle in this good of shape and with such a history, I'd rather not shoot it.  It's not a "show" piece, but the rifle is in excellent condition.  Anyone who knows M1's knows the Winchester was a special model as they were only made during WWII and don't use the cast parts that SA, IH and HR switched to at the time.  As far as I can tell, all of the parts are original.  A good friend of mine who is a gunsmith had disassembled the rifle and had gone through all of the parts and said it was in great condition considering its age!  The stock isn't perfect, but there are no chunks taken out, and as far as we know, it's an original stock.  

Rifle comes with a new sling.  If I get close to my asking price, I'll include the case.  If I get my asking price, I'll throw in 80rds of 30-06 preloaded in the M1 clips. title: For Sale:   Engraved Belgian Pinfire Pepperbox
postcontent:
The multi-barreled pepperbox designs from the first half of the 19th century provided the first reliable revolving firearm system for the average citizen to purchase and carry for self protection. The development of the self-contained, pinfire cartridge by Casimir Lefaucheux in 1836 would dramatically affect the popularity of the pepperbox in coming decades. 

The success of the cartridge system and the revolver spawned hundreds of variations, copies, improvements and outright patent infringements on the Lefaucheux design throughout Europe, especially in France and Belgium.

Everything appears to be mechanically sound and firearm locks up correctly when hammer is let down. Frame and cylinder construction appears to be of either brass or bronze alloy, hammer and trigger are steel. Grips are of a European Burlwood and show rich grain, appears to still have the original finish intact on 80%+. Original fired casing "ejector rod" is threaded into the bottom of the grip.

Weight: 1.5 Lbs

title: For Sale:  Competitive Muzzleloader Pistol Shooting
postcontent: If you've ever shown an interest or had a want to shoot NRA Bullseye Pistol but could never afford the amount of ammunition necessary to practice enough to excel then give bullseye with muzzleloaders a thought. The National Championships are in Friendship Indianna at the NMLRA (National Muzzle Loading Rifle Association) headquarters on their range. The program or course of fire closely imitates the conventioal bullseye program. A 25 yard slow fire target And a 25 yard timed fire target and a 50 yard slow fire target make up an agg for the caplock pistol and that course of fire is also fired with a flintlock pistol. The percusion revolver is the same with an additional 25 meter international target at 25 yards. This makes up a 1000 point match. Ammunition and components are cheaper than conventional pistol and easier to find. Give blackpowder bullseye pistol some thought. Contact me with questions. Local competition could be available with enough interest. At least call or email me and you could test fire my guns. That might give you more insight to the sport.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Gold
postcontent:
I have about 3 ounces of scrap gold I'm looking to trade. Most is rings and chains. All but 2 pieces is stamped with its purity. I Have acid tested all of the gold. The marks are correct. Here's a list of what I have..... 

10k gold: 1.155 grams 
12k gold: 16.700 grams 
14k gold: 85.810 grams 
16k gold: 4 grams 

Calculated down to melt value of pure gold in ounces: (weighed with a standard scale, this is not Troy ounces, just standard ounces.) 

10k gold: 0.0154. $17.94 
12k gold: 0.2683. $313.56 
14k gold: 1.6070. $1,878.11 
16k gold: 0.0858. $100.16 

Total market value: $2309.77 

For a cost of about $100 it can be smelted down to a bar of pure 24k gold in the weight of about 1.9756 ounce. Market value of it is about $2300 depending on when you do the calculations. 

With gold value always changing I'm setting my trade value at $1600. If I get a chance to take my gold to the smelter before trading it off the price will change. I just wanted to try listing it before I smelt and sell it outright. I can acid test it in front of you to show purity

No I will not just sell the gold as is. My plan is to try to trade it or next week I'm going to smelt it and have it poured into a solid 2 ounce bar. 

Now for what I'm looking for. I'm really looking for guns, AR's, bolt actions, lever actions, pistols. I will also trade for ammo, reloading supplies, gun safes, hunting equipment, night vision.  As for specifics..... I'm looking for ar's in 458 socom, 50 beuwolf, 338 federal, 308, 6.8 spc, 6.5 Grendel, any wildcats as long as they come with reloading dies.  454 casull revolvers, single action 357's, Winchester model 70's, Remington 700's, 1911's, 338 lapua, long range 300 win mag. For lever actions I'll take pistol calibers, 35 remington, any big bore but no 30-30's.  I'm sure there's a lot more so email me any trade offers.

title: For Sale:   Cold Steel Rajah III
postcontent: The Rajah folders designed by Andrew Demko, are big enough to approximate and feel and heft a fixed blade Kukri.
